Japan's Apology and Compensation for "Comfort Women" Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- The Council for the Solution of the Issue of the Volunteers Corps of south Korea has recently conducted an international signature campaign urging the Japanese government to apologize and compensate to the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese Army, according to the KBS of south Korea on July 17.
The campaign conducted by the council in different countries on the theme of "Justice for the old women who were forced to serve as comfort women for the imperial Japanese Army" is not only urging the settlement of the issue of the "comfort women" but strongly opposing Japan's bid for permanent membership of the UNSC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Up to now 550,000 people in different countries and regions of the world are reported to have participated in the campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The council made it clear that it would convey the signature paper to the UN secretary general.

Month of International Solidarity with Korean People Closes in Cuba 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- A closing ceremony of the month of international solidarity with the Korean people was held on July 15 under the co-sponsorship of the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and the Cuban Association for Friendship with Peoples.
 Present there were Juan Jose Leon Vega, chairman of the committee, and officials of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba, the Committee for Defending the Cuban Revolution and the association and citizens of Havana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony on invitation were the DPRK ambassador and staff members of its embassy in Havana. 
 Jose Manuel Garcia, director for External Affairs of the Committee for Defending the Cuban Revolution, said that the U.S., the common enemy of Cuba and the DPRK, is getting more desperate in its moves to stifle the two countries, adding that those frantic moves of the U.S. only reinforce the bilateral friendship and solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that with no machination can the U.S. isolate and stifle the DPRK founded by President Kim Il Sung, he stressed that the fraternal Cuban people fully support the Korean people in their just struggle to foil the U.S. imperialists' moves against the DPRK, defend the sovereignty of the country and reunify the country independently and peacefully.

Military Attaches Corps Visit Victorious Fatherland Liberation War Museum 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited the Victorious Fatherland Liberation War Museum on July 20 on the occasion of the 52nd anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War.
 The guests went round the relics on display with keen interest, being briefed on the fact that President Kim Il Sung set out the Juche-oriented military thought and original strategic and tactical policies, leading the whole party and army and all the people to brilliant victory in the sacred battles against the U.S. during the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the visit a meeting between members of the corps and heroes of the Republic took place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting General Officers of the KPA Ko Kyong Sik, Kim Kun Ok and Pak Chan Su who are heroes of the Republic recalled with deep emotion the days they defeated U.S. imperialism that had boasted of "being the strongest" in the world and won great victory in the war under the leadership of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the army and people of Korea would as ever display to the full the spirit of heroic Korea and surely build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation on this land under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander born of Heaven. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nguyen Van Chau, Vietnamese military attache, warmly congratulated the servicepersons of the KPA on the anniversary on behalf of the corps, hoping that the army and people of Korea would register great success in defending the country and building socialism under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Anti-Japanese Meetings Go on 
