 The venues of meetings were packed with crowds whose hearts were burning with hatred for the Japanese reactionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reporters and speakers at meetings held by employees of the Kim Jong Thae Electric Locomotive Plant, the Chongjin Thermal-Power Plant and the Phyongsong Taesong Knitted Goods Factory denounced the Japanese imperialists�f usurpation of the sovereignty of Korea as an act of aggression in defiance of international law and intolerable hideous crime, recalling that this year marks the centenary of the brigandish fabrication of the �gUlsa Five-Point Treaty�h by the wicked Japanese imperialist aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reporters and speakers at the meetings held by Phyongsong University of Coal Mining, Kim Jong Thae Haeju University of Education No. 1, Hamhung University of Chemical Engineering and Wonsan University of Medicine pointed out that the Japanese reactionaries�f evermore undisguised distortion of history textbooks, their moves to grab Tok Islet and their reckless remarks concerning Japan�fs colonial rule over Korea, etc. irrefutably prove that Japan�fs intention to stage a comeback to Korea and its militarist ambition has gone beyond the danger line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting held at the September Textile Mill warned that the Japanese reactionaries will meet destruction only if they persistently pursue their anachronistic hostile policy toward the DPRK and go on with their rash actions over the �gnuclear issue�h and �gabduction issue�h in support of the U.S. imperialists�f moves to stifle the DPRK.

Egyptian Diplomats Help Korean Farmers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter, Egyptian ambassador to the DPRK, and his embassy officials gave helping hands to the DPRK-Egypt Friendship Sosamjong Co-op Farm on the outskirts of Pyongyang on July 20.
 After being briefed on the history of the farm in front of the monument to the on-the-spot instructions given by President Kim Il Sung, they joined farmers in weeding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During break, they talked to one another and sang together, deepening the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador said they learned that Kim Il Sung visited the farm several times to give instructions for increasing the agricultural production and Kim Jong Il has wisely led the drive to build the DPRK into the best country. He wished the farmers great success in the agricultural production this year. 
 Then, they handed aid materials to the farm.

Attempts to Stamp Out Cause of Socialism Termed Day-Dream
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Socialism is the ideal of humankind and represents its future.
 Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ideal of humankind is to live independently and happily and develop on an equal footing in the peaceful world free from all sorts of exploitation and oppression, domination and subordination and war and aggression. It is precisely the socialist idea that meets the common demand and aspiration of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the noble purpose and mission of socialism to oppose the exploitation of man by man and all sorts of domination and subordination, respect and guarantee the sovereignty of all countries and nations and struggle to meet the intrinsic demand of humankind and their wishes to live and develop independently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The popular masses can be independent, all the countries and nations can achieve their independent development and human civilization make progress only when they advance along the road of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists and venal hack writers are busy spreading misinformation about the ideal of socialism in a bid to shake the faith in socialism among the revolutionary people of the world and create an illusion about capitalism and thus stop history advancing. This is a blatant challenge to the ideal of humankind and the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists and all hues of reactionaries of history are desperately working to stamp out the cause of socialism, but it is nothing but an anachronistic daydream. People are still aspiring after and advancing toward independence and socialism.
 The ideal of humankind is sure to come true as it is immortal.

Korean Writers Meet to Implement June 15 Joint Declaration
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- A meeting of Korean writers for implementing the June 15 joint declaration was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Wednesday.
 Present there were Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol, Chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of the Unions of Literature and the Arts of Korea Kim Jong Ho, writers and poets in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by the south side's delegation led by Ko Un, chairman for reunification of the Association of Men of National Literature, a delegation of Korean writers in Japan led by Kim Jong Su, chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the Union of Korean Writers and Artistes in Japan (UKWAJ), and Han Kil Su, department director of the General Association of Koreans in China, and his party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Pyong Hun, chairman of the C.C., the Korean Writers Union (KWU), made an opening address at the meeting before the introduction of congratulatory letters and messages from various compatriots organizations in the north and the south of Korea and overseas and literary organizations and men of literature in different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In his congratulatory speech, Ro Tu Chol said that the 70 million Koreans follow with deep interest the meeting of Korean writers, the first of its kind in 60 years of national division, hoping that it would mark a historic occasion of greatly contributing to the reunification of the country and the development of national literature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the writers, he said, should produce successful works meeting the need of the era after the publication of the June 15 joint declaration so as to help all the fellow countrymen cherish more deeply the idea of "By our nation itself", the spirit of national independence, and thus positively contribute to the great unity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Paek Rak Chong, chairman of the south side's preparatory committee under the June 15 Joint Committee, said in his congratulatory speech that this meeting has brought into sight a new type of Korean literature that would inspire the entire nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting, Vice-Chairman of the KWU Central Committee Kim Tok Chol, poet Ri Si Yong who is a delegate of the south side, and Chairman of the UKWAJ Central Standing Committee Kim Jong Su made reports under the subjects of "On duty and role of writers of national literature in the June 15 reunification era", "On the formation of the 'June 15 Association of Men of National Literature'" and "On instituting the 'June 15 Prize for Reunification Literature'". Then followed speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A five-point declaration of the meeting was adopted. The declaration said:
 First. We, Korean writers will regard the June 15 Joint Declaration as the only landmark for national reunification and resolutely defend and implement it to the last.
 Second. We, Korean writers will turn out to create literary works in the spirit of national independence, peace against war and reunification and patriotism under the banner of "By our nation itself". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Third. We, Korean writers will unite close irrespective of ideology, religion, birthplace and political stand and intensify solidarity and unity in activities for national literature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fourth. We will form the "June 15 Association of Men of National Literature as a joint organization of Korean literary men at home and abroad and take an active part in its activities and edit and publish its organ "Reunification Literature" well to serve as a close companion of all our fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fifth. We fully support the proposal for awarding the "June 15 Prize for Reunification Literature" to those who make a literary contribution to national reunification as a commendation to be made on behalf of the nation and will work hard to have the honor of receiving the prize. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the south side's delegation in his closing address said that the meeting represented the desire for the festival of national literature whose final goal is to reunify the country.

Participants in Meeting of Korean Writers Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Korean Writers Union hosted a reception for the participants in the  meeting of Korean writers for implementing the June 15 joint declaration at the People's Palace of Culture on Wednesday evening.
 Present on invitation were a delegation of the south side led by Chairman for Reunification of the Association of Men of National Literature Ko Un, a delegation of Korean writers in Japan headed by Chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the Union of Korean Writers and Artistes in Japan Kim Jong Su and Department Director of the General Association of Koreans in China Han Kil Su and his party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol, Director of the Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland An Kyong Ho, Chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of the Unions of Literature and the Arts of Korea Kim Jong Ho, Chairman of the KWU Central Committee Kim Pyong Hun and officials concerned, writers and poets in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made and a performance of the north's artistes given at the reception.

Anti-U.S. and Anti-War Function Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- An anti-U.S. and anti-war function reportedly took place at Maroni Park, Seoul, on July 16 under the sponsorship of the Youth and Student Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration, the Northern Branch of the Youth Association for Loving the Country and the Federation of University Student Councils of the Northern District of Seoul under the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils.
 Its participants conducted information activities among citizens holding umbrellas bearing anti-U.S. and anti-war slogans before  setting up slogan boards condemning the United States for its nuclear war scenario and its arms build-up and killings of civilians committed by the U.S. troops in south Korea in the street and lanes leading to the park, distributing leaflets among citizens and conducting an all-people signature campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citizens gathered around the slogan boards and wrote letters reflecting their resolution to struggle against the U.S. and war and for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops before participating in the signature campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When somebody put a question as to which country they dislike most, citizens replied: It's the United States. They demanded an immediate withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea, denouncing them for killing two schoolgirls Hyo Sun and Mi Son and other atrocities perpetrated by them.

National Holiday of Egypt Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- A friendship gathering with staff members of the Egyptian embassy here was held at DPRK-Egypt Friendship Kim Song Ju Primary School in Pyongyang on July 20 to mark the 53rd anniversary of the July 23 Revolution in Egypt, the national holiday of the Egyptian people.
 Invited there were Egyptian Ambassador Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter and his embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They laid bouquets before President Kim Il Sung's statue standing at the school and paid tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the history of the school associated with leadership exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu, they went round educational facilities of the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the gathering enjoyed an art performance given by schoolchildren and talked to each other about further development of the DPRK-Egypt relations, deepening friendship.

Pyongsu Joint Venture Company
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- The Pyongsu (Pyongyang-Swiss) Joint Venture Company situated in Pyongyang produces various kinds of medicines to suit GMP (Good Manufacturing Practice).
 It, which has produced Pyongsuspirin (aspirin), will shortly start to manufacture anodynes such as Pyongsucetamol (paracetamol) and Pyongsuprofen (ibuprofen) and antibiotic medicines including doxycycline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company was founded in June Juche 93 (2004) with the joint investment of the Pyongyang Pharmaceutical Plant under the DPRK Ministry of Public Health and the North Development Corporation supported by Swiss Inter Pacific Holding Group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its deputy manager O Song Gun told KCNA that the buildings, environment, sanitation and medicine quality examination of the company fully suit GMP. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its pharmaceutical plant is furnished with latest machines and equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the production processes are controlled by SOP (Standard Operating Procedure).

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 21 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected KPA Unit 2653.
 After going round the room devoted to the history of the unit, he said the unit has grown to be matchless combat ranks under the wise leadership and meticulous care of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the unit's performance of duty before watching servicepersons' training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was satisfied to learn that all the servicepersons of the unit have been trained as a-match-for-a-hundred fighters fully prepared politically, ideologically and physically and in military technique to firmly defend the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the thick woodland around the barracks, he praised its servicepersons for having carefully planted and tended lots of trees of various species with ardent patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He taught ways of turning their compound into a wooded area under a long-term plan.
 He learned about how the political work is conducted at the unit, looking round the servicepersons' hall, a library, a broadcasting room and other entertainment facilities.
 Examining the diverse visual aids for education on display in the servicepersons' hall, he said the People's Army is conducting any political work in a unique manner to suit the mentality and emotion of the soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such forward-looking and revolutionary work style as steadily creating something and making innovations without even a moment's stagnation and marking time constitutes a proud tradition consistently preserved by our army, the standard-bearer and a shock force for the Songun revolution, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the servicepersons' living, going round a mess hall, a kitchen, a non-staple food store and other logistic facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking at the menu on display in the mess hall and materials for preparing side-dishes on the meshwork stand with keen attention, he underscored the need to serve plenty of fresh food to the soldiers engrossed in the training without having time enough to dry their uniforms wet with perspiration in the sultry summer days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of its Central Committee, and Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of its Central Committee.
